name: lazypredict
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "lazypredict" %}
{% set version = "0.2.9" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/lazypredict-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 453853175517bd4b928c7122c39714688208f0e66dc4e9d7c1a945433f157158

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - lazypredict=lazypredict.cli:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - pytest-runner
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - click ==7.1.2
    - joblib ==1.0.0
    - lightgbm ==2.3.1
    - numpy ==1.19.1
    - pandas ==1.0.5
    - pytest ==5.4.3
    - python >=3.6
    - pyyaml ==5.3.1
    - scikit-learn ==0.23.1
    - scipy >=1.5.3
    - six ==1.15.0
    - tqdm ==4.56.0
    - xgboost >=1.1.1

test:
  imports:
    - lazypredict
  commands:
    - lazypredict --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/shankarpandala/lazypredict
  summary: Rapid low code ML testing with multiple basic models
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  description: |
    Lazy Predict help build a lot of basic models without much code and helps
     understand which models works better without any parameter tuning

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thewchan
